@node "appsetup" "APPSetup"

  APPSetup is the program that is ued to setup each users user id's and passwords and the other
  details reuired by APPS.

  It uses the same Inteface file as APPS so they both have the same look and feel.

  You use the same version of APPSetup for both the standard and Pro version of APPS the standard
  version innores the etra code any way.

  Here is a description of strings in APPSetup.


  User Id -  This is the users identity code it can be anything upto 8 charcters long.  It is also used for as the suffix for the user logon file.

  Password - This is the users own password.  This to can be upto 8 charcters but best to use either letters or number.

  User Name - This is the users real name.  It used by the User Information program.  Not implemented yet in this version.

  User AKA - This is the users AKA, Alias, Nickname, Handle. (Also not implemtented)

  Mount device -  This is the name of the device assigned to each user.  This is only found in the pro version as it requires a lot of setimg up.

  Startup-sequence - This is the file which stores ech users boot of script. This can be any file anywhere.  The stanadard startup-sequence is copied, renamed and replaced during installation but can be used here.

  The Buttons are as Follows:

  New - Clears all string gadgets and starts from new

  Load - Reads the user Id String and load the file accordingly

  Save - Reads the all strings gadgets, adds the extra code and saves the file using the user id
  string as the suffix for the users file.

  Help - Opens a scrollable help window with a quick description of the string gadgets
  
  Quit - Ends the Program

 REMEMBER - The load function needs the users id to be input into the user id string gadget
@endnode

