@node "PRO" "Pro Version Doc"

   The PRO version of APPS requires more setup than the standard version as it reuires hard drives to partitioned and mountlists to be created.  This not a task for the faint hearted.

  Users can do this the easiest way they an but waht they need to do is to :

  a.  Partition their hard drive to give each users their own drive.  They then need to install
      workbench and any and all programs that the requires.

  b.  The mountfile on the needs to be editied to include all the drive information for each
      partition. This really needs to be there or APPS chuccks a mental.

  c. depeneding on your trust of the user then you need to edit their startup-sequence to do the
     following.

                  1. Move system assigns to their drive including fonts,s,libs etc.

                  2. use the assign command to dismount the boot device and remove it from the
                     amigados volumes list. This will stop the user from accessing your drive and
                     mountlist.

    If you trsut yours users not to mess around with your drive then the abouve is not needed.


  The best option is to create a small boot device of about 10mb and install only Workbench and APPS on it and use your own partiton in the same way.

  The above maybe added to futre version of APPS Pro depending on the complexity and whether i keep Pro working in the same way.

 Note! There is a Porgram called "MoveSys" which moves all the sys: assigns to the selected drive.
       You Might find this useful.
@endnode

